      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a small drizzle of <strong>olive oil </strong>over a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>sliced onion</strong>, <strong>half</strong> your <strong>balsamic vinegar </strong>(you'll use the rest later!) with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>sugar</strong></p><p>Reduce the heat to very low and cook for 10-12 min or until softened and caramelised – this is your <strong>balsamic caramelised onion</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1724229737900-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
